quran[33]{c,v,t}:
  55,46,But for he who feared to be one day in the Presence of his Lord are two Gardens
  55,47,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,48,With shading branches
  55,49,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,50,In them are two flowing springs
  55,51,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,52,and they have pairs of every kind of fruits
  55,53,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,54,"They will be reclining on couches lined with silk brocade, and the fruit of the two Gardens are near at hand"
  55,55,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,56,"In them are creature-mates of modest gaze, untouched before them by man or jinn"
  55,57,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,58,As though they were rubies and coral
  55,59,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,60,Will the reward for goodness be anything but goodness
  55,61,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,62,And beneath them are two other gardens
  55,63,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,64,Dark green
  55,65,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,66,With two gushing springs
  55,67,So which of your Lord's blessings do you both deny
  55,68,"In them are fruits, date-palms and pomegranates"
  55,69,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,70,In them are sweet and lovely creatures
  55,71,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,72,"Hoor, kept close in their pavilions"
  55,73,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,74,Untouched before them by man or jinn
  55,75,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,76,Reclining on green cushions and beautiful fine carpets
  55,77,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,78,"Blessed be the name of your Lord, full of Majesty and Glory"